cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper deals with medical imaging and computer vision techniques for prostate cancer diagnosis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of a fully convolutional network also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging and diagnosis, which could place it in cs.MED (Medical Imaging). The use of a novel segmentation technique could also suggest that the paper belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
